com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.net
Interface L2Interface

All Superinterfaces:
com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability, com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.DeployModelObject, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Implementing Classes:
L2InterfaceImpl
public interface L2Interface
extends com.ibm.ccl.soa.deploy.core.Capability

A representation of the model object 'L2 Interface'.

The following features are supported:

  • Auto Negotiation
  • Broadcast
  • Duplex
  • Encapsulation
  • Hw Address
  • Index
  • L2 Interface Name
  • Loopback
  • Mtu
  • Private
  • Promiscuous
  • Speed

See Also:
NetPackage.getL2Interface()

getL2InterfaceName

java.lang.String getL2InterfaceName()
Returns the value of the 'L2 Interface Name' attribute. Name of the interface. This can vary depending on the Operating System and how the data is collected. SNMP - This field corresponds to the ifName Windows - This attribute corresponds to the "Name" column on the Network Connections panel. The "Device Name" column should not be used since a Computer System may have more than one adapter with the same Device Name. The "Name" column is globally unique. For Unix based systems this atttribute corresponds to the ifConfig value. It should be something like en0.

Returns:
the value of the 'L2 Interface Name' attribute.
See Also:
setL2InterfaceName(String), NetPackage.getL2Interface_L2InterfaceName()
